column49: The new ordering format is not very inclusive to the demographic of my school. Many families in my school do not have access to the internet or use cash payments for everything due to circumstances beyond their control. This means that many students would like to be able to pay for books with cash and this option seems to have been removed since the only options on my end are to place a teacher order (and make sure I keep very clear notes as to who ordered what) or not allow families to order with cash anymore. I feel like it would be helpful to go back to the old system where there is still an option for online family orders, but also a place for teachers to place student orders.

column49: This is not feedback on the website, but I have feed back on the new way that the scholastic book orders are done. I have seen a major decline in my students ordering books this year. The students at my school have always loved to order books. They have always relied heavily on me as the teacher ordering the books though. Since we have made the switch none of my students have ordered any books. I did have 3 students try to bring me money for me to order like we did in the past, but since my teacher order now has shipping and taxes added to it,  I am not able to do their order that way. We live in an area where technology is not reliable and a lot of families are not able to access the internet from their homes. So I feel my students are at an unfair advantage and will no longer be able to utilize scholastic book clubs.
